Emotional support

1 Description of DataSchema variable

The description of harmonised variable is the following:

  • Short name: emot_sup
  • Variable label: Receives emotional support from someone
  • Variable description: Receives emotional support from someone (i.e. has someone to count on, people show concern in what s/he is doing, etc.)
  • Domain: Social environment
  • Value type: categorical
  • Category coding:
Code Category Label
0 No
1 Yes
  • Category missings:
Code Category Label
991 CAPI/interviewer error
992 Impute
993 Disable to measure
994 Not attempt/not done
995 Does not answer
996 Not applicable
997 Refuse
998 Do not know
999 Missing

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if any variable equals 1 or 2 then 1
  • if all are equal 3 or 4 then 0
  • -1 into 996
  • -9 into 995
  • NA into 999

R script:

ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1_emot_sup$id)

ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc), "NA='-999'")


ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup <- c(NA)
for (i in 1:dim(ELSA_w1_emot_sup)[1]) {
    if (ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2)) {
        ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup[i] = 1
    } else if (ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb[i] == 
        -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda[i] == 
        -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc[i] == 
        -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb[i] == 
        -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda[i] == 
        -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] == -1 & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] == 
        -1) {
        ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup[i] = 996
    } else if (ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1)) {
        ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup[i] = 0
    } else if (ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptra[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrb[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scptrc[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchda[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdb[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scchdc[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfama[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamb[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfamc[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrda[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] == -9 | ELSA_w1_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] == 
        -9) {
        ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup[i] = 995
    }
}

ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_ds_w1$emot_sup), "NA='999'")

2.1.3.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if any variable equals 1 or 2 then 1
  • if all are equal 3 or 4 then 0
  • -1 into 996
  • -8 into 998
  • -9 into 995
  • NA into 999

R script:

ELSA_ds_w3 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w3_emot_sup$id)

ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb), "NA='-999'")
ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc), "NA='-999'")


ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup <- c(NA)
for (i in 1:dim(ELSA_w3_emot_sup)[1]) {
    if (ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] %in% c(1, 2) | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] %in% 
        c(1, 2)) {
        ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup[i] = 1
    } else if (ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] %in% c(3, 4, -1) & ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] %in% 
        c(3, 4, -1)) {
        ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup[i] = 0
    } else if (ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb[i] == 
        -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda[i] == 
        -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc[i] == 
        -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb[i] == 
        -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda[i] == 
        -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] == -1 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] == 
        -1) {
        ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup[i] = 996
    } else if (ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda[i] == 
        -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] == -9 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] == 
        -9) {
        ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup[i] = 995
    } else if (ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptra[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrb[i] == 
        -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scptrc[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchda[i] == 
        -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdb[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scchdc[i] == 
        -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfama[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamb[i] == 
        -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfamc[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrda[i] == 
        -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdb[i] == -8 | ELSA_w3_emot_sup$scfrdc[i] == 
        -8) {
        ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup[i] = 998
    }
}

ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup <- car::recode(as.vector(ELSA_ds_w3$emot_sup), "NA='999'")

2.1.5.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if any variable equals 1 or 2 then 1
  • if all are equal 3 or 4 then 0
  • -1 or -2 into 996
  • -8 into 998
  • -9 into 995
  • NA into 999

2.1.7.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable from the study-specific variable it has to be recoded as follows:

  • if any variable equals 1 or 2 then 1
  • if all are equal 3 or 4 then 0
  • -1 or -2 into 996
  • -8 into 998
  • -9 into 995
  • NA into 999
